The Weather Whisperer\line
\b\fs28\line
\b0\fs24
Old guides say: watch the barometer like a hawk watches a field mouse.\line
\line
Rising slowly? Fish will be lazy but catchable. Use small presentations.\line
Falling fast? Storm coming — fish feed aggressively before the pressure tanks.\line
Steady for three days? Pick a different hobby.\line
\line
\b Signs to read without instruments:\b0\line
- Swallows flying low → rain within hours (and poor fishing)\line
- Smoke from campfire curls downward → stable air, good for topwater action\line
- Cows lying down in a field → you may not catch fish, but at least you're not a cow\line
\line
\i The best weather forecast is a sore shoulder from yesterday's casting.\i0\line
\line
Remember: you can't control the wind. But you can learn to curse it in three languages.\line
